description.text: The Camino del Norte follows the Northen coastline of Spain. This route follows the Via Agrippa for some of its way, which was used in the Middle Ages by Christian pilgrims when travel along the French Way was dangerous.@en

notes.text: Many locations on the Camino del Norte are holiday destinations with numerous accommodation options. Many towns have generic accommodation types listed, rather than a long list of all options.@en
There is a link to the Camino Primitivo at Villaviciosa. To use this, set the finish point to Villaviciosa and then make a separate plan for the Primitivo.@en
The starting pooint for those wishing to make the 100km pilgrimage is Baamonde.@en

The sendero de gran recorrido (GR) paths are a series of long distance footpaths in Europe. The E9 European long distance path follows the Northern coast of Europe. This route follows the E9 for a short distance along the coast.
